# Copy to `.env` and adjust. The white-label build bakes these per school.
#
# API_BASE: the backend origin. The mobile API is host-agnostic (tenant resolved
# from the JWT user), so any reachable origin works. Use the dev box for testing.
API_BASE=https://dev-mse.ecoursale.com

# SCHOOL_CODE: optional hint shown on the login screen / used for deep links. The
# actual tenant is always resolved server-side from the logged-in user, NOT this.
SCHOOL_CODE=mse

# APP_NAME: launcher/display name fallback (real branding comes from /school/config).
APP_NAME=Ecoursale

# GOOGLE_SERVER_CLIENT_ID: the Google WEB OAuth client id used as `serverClientId`
# for native "Continue with Google". OPTIONAL — leave blank for the platform
# school: the backend serves its own client id via /school/config (google_oauth_
# client_id, which falls back to the backend's GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID). Set this
# only for a white-label build that should use a *different* Google project than
# what /school/config returns. Empty everywhere → the button is hidden.
# An Android OAuth client (package com.ecoursale.ecoursale_app + the signing
# SHA-1) must exist in the SAME Google project, or sign-in fails after the button.
#GOOGLE_SERVER_CLIENT_ID=

